      "span_text": "The available evidence suggests that catalepsy mainly originates from a blockade of D 1 or D 2 receptors in the caudate-putamen (CP) or a decreased presynaptic DA activity in this structure, since intrastriatal infusions of DA-antagonists (Elliott et al., 1990 a;  , 6-hydroxydopamine-lesions of the mesostriatal DA system or reserpine treatment produced catalepsy (see Schmidt etal., 1992 for review)."
